HEADWORD: Arecidae
<hw>Arecidae</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fr>1</fr> <def>one of four
subclasses or superorder of Monocotyledones; comprises about 6400
species in 5 families of trees and shrubs and terrestrial herbs and a
few free-floating aquatics including: Palmae; Araceae; Pandanaceae: and
Lemnaceae.</def>⟦br⟧
